Class Move.PawnJump

java.lang.Object
engine.forBoard.Move
engine.forBoard.Move.PawnJump
Enclosing class:
Move
public static class Move.PawnJump extends Move
The PawnJump class represents a pawn move where a pawn advances two squares from its starting position. This special move is only available on a pawn's first move and creates an en passant opportunity for opponent pawns on adjacent files.
Author:
Aaron Ho

      public Board execute()
      Executes the pawn jump move, updating the board accordingly. This method creates a new board with the pawn moved to the destination coordinate, an en passant pawn set, and the move transition recorded.
